description: The smooth white walls throw contrast to the steel floor on which
you stand on.  The floor, marked by strange black signs, seems to be a
receptacle for the Partition transport system.  There is an audible
voice eminating from the ceiling calling out:
'{^Welcome to Tenhauser Gate.{x'
'{^Please exercise caution, there are many security systems around the complex, if you{x'
'{^are not cleared to enter, or have gotten here by error, just step forward, and you{x'
'{^will be released back to the surface. If you are a cleared user, please wear your{x'
'{^access badge on your person.  Thank you for your presence, we wish you well.{x'
'{^Warning to spellcasters:  Due to the Tenhauser Gate's shielding system and{x'
'{^it's disconnected proximity to the realms, magic will be innefective during your{x'
'{^Stay with us.  We will provide all necessary commodities and services to compensate{x'
'{%Thank you, and have a safe and productive day{x'

description: Many people come and go on the escalator-lifts provided by the
Tenhauser Facility.  Two {%D{*C{%D{7 officers stand by the lifts keeping the
peace.  The escalators seem to work on some type of loco-motion
mechanics, but the system seems to be made of solid, yet dimmed light.

description: The first security zone consists of little more than a strange
futuristic hall with an intricate surveillance system and a floating
globe of light.  THe orb emits a high pitch pulsating noise
sporadically, as it seems to be communicating with something or other.
As you approach, a brief tone emits from the hallway, and the orb
seems to turn in place.
'{!Attention, you are to remain in place until a type-02 security sweep is preformed{x'
37601.name: Secure Access Tunnel

god's eye view.  It's hard not to feel insignificant when comparing
the planet to the universe, but it is still pleasing to the eye to see
the oceans contrasting the earth.
